      <PrimaryExemptPurposeTxt>To promote transportation solutions that protect and support a healthy environment healthy people healthy communities and a healthy economy.</PrimaryExemptPurposeTxt>
      <ProgramSrvcAccomplishmentGrp>
        <DescriptionProgramSrvcAccomTxt>Street Story promotion: Street Story is a public platform for crowdsourcing street safety information which is then used for planning and advocating for safety improvements. Our work involved analyzing Street Story reports made in Humboldt County through March 2024 educating the public about Street Story using a variety of strategies providing technical assistance and training to local agencies and community groups and attending and disseminating information about using the Street Story tool at community events and meetings.</DescriptionProgramSrvcAccomTxt>
        <GrantsAndAllocationsAmt>30000</GrantsAndAllocationsAmt>
        <ProgramServiceExpensesAmt>30000</ProgramServiceExpensesAmt>
      </ProgramSrvcAccomplishmentGrp>
      <ProgramSrvcAccomplishmentGrp>
        <DescriptionProgramSrvcAccomTxt>Transit rider organizing: We talked to riders at bus stops and on buses asked them about their experiences with local public transit and their needs and desires for improvements to the transit system connected riders with each other via in-person events and social media coordinated riders with local decision-makers to ride local transit together and kept riders informed and engaged with opportunities to advocate for transit improvements.</DescriptionProgramSrvcAccomTxt>
        <GrantsAndAllocationsAmt>15000</GrantsAndAllocationsAmt>
        <ProgramServiceExpensesAmt>15000</ProgramServiceExpensesAmt>
      </ProgramSrvcAccomplishmentGrp>
      <ProgramSrvcAccomplishmentGrp>
        <DescriptionProgramSrvcAccomTxt>Public education and advocacy for safe sustainable and equitable transportation: We used email social media and in-person engagement to provide information to members of the public about local transportation plans and projects research-based transportation planning concepts and principles and related topics. We advocated for safer more environmentally sound and more equitable transportation systems.</DescriptionProgramSrvcAccomTxt>
        <GrantsAndAllocationsAmt>0</GrantsAndAllocationsAmt>
        <ProgramServiceExpensesAmt>24000</ProgramServiceExpensesAmt>
      </ProgramSrvcAccomplishmentGrp>
